infos.info: The Bing Crosby Show went on the air after Crosby left the Kraft Music Hall in the spring of 1946, when Kraft refused to let him record his shows. - First series called ' Fifteen Minutes with Bing Crosby,' - Second series on various days. - Third series called ' The Music that Satisfies.' - Philco sponsored show called: ' Philco Radio Time.' - 1949-52 Chesterfield sponsored show called: ' The Bing Crosby Chesterfield Show.' - General Electric sponsored show called: ' The General Electric Show.' - Terrace lists the show ending in 1962, and the following as regulars: - Connie Boswell, Rosemary Clooney, Peggy Lee, Bob Burns, Jud Comlon's Rhythmaries, The Red Nichols Combo, Skitch Henderson, The Buddy Cole Trio and Glenn Riggs as one of the announcers, and John Scott Trotter as the orchestra leader. - Terrace lists the BROADCAST HISTORY as 1931 (NBC), later on CBS, ended in 1962
